"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:4.6.3\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">4.6.3</span> 标题：铸像（molten image）</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">经文出处</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：מַסֵּכָה</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：masekah)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:4\">EXO 32:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod32:8\">EXO 32:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod34:17\">EXO 34:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev19:4\">LEV 19:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num33:52\">NUM 33:52</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:12\">DEU 9:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut9:16\">DEU 9:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:15\">DEU 27:15</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:3\">JDG 17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg17:4\">JDG 17:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:14\">JDG 18:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:17\">JDG 18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg18:18\">JDG 18:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs14:9\">1KI 14:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Kgs17:16\">2KI 17:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr28:2\">2CH 28:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:3\">2CH 34:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr34:4\">2CH 34:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:18\">NEH 9:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps106:19\">PSA 106:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa30:22\">ISA 30:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa42:17\">ISA 42:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos13:2\">HOS 13:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:14\">NAM 1:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:18\">HAB 2:18</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：נָסִיךְ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：nasik)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan11:8\">DAN 11:8</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">来：נֶסֶךְ</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(音译：nesek)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa41:29\">ISA 41:29</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:5\">ISA 48:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:14\">JER 10:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer51:17\">JER 51:17</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">描述</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>铸像是把熔融的金属倒进模具来制成的偶像，这些像的大小和形状可能相差很大。参上文<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">4.6.1 家中的神像、家神的像 (teraphim, household idol)&lt;REALIA:4.6.1&gt;</a> 插图所示的像及其模具。</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">翻译</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>上文列出的希伯来文词语表示“倒”的动作，事实上，<em>nesek</em> 一词更多是指倒出来的浇酒祭或奠祭（参<a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">9.1 酒、葡萄酒 (wine)&lt;REALIA:9.1&gt;</a> ）。有些译本尝试用“浇铸的”或“铸造的”等修饰语来反映这一点。在大多数经文中，使用“偶像”的统称就足够了。</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah1:14\">NAM 1:14</a> ：这节经文和其他经文提到了两种神像。 雕刻的偶像是用石头或（更普遍地）用木头雕刻而成的。铸造的偶像是把熔融的金属倒入模具铸成的。现今的语言很少有专门的词语分别指这两种不同的像。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Revised English Bible (1989)\">REB</abbr> 使用了两个词，即“image and idol”（“像和偶像”），但这样做不是特别必要。在希伯来文中，这两个词一起使用是指所有种类的神像（比较<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut27:15\">DEU 27:15</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa48:5\">ISA 48:5</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer10:14\">JER 10:14</a> ；<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hab2:18\">HAB 2:18</a> ），翻译者选用这些神像的一个统称就够了（其制造方式没有任何属灵意义）。<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> 只使用了一个词“idols”（“偶像”）。有些译本用简单的言语就表达出这两个不同的对象；例如，“雕刻的像和铸造的偶像”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"New International Version (1984)\">NIV</abbr> 直译），“木头和金属［制成”的偶像”（<abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Italian Common Language Version\">ITCL</abbr> 直译）。</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
